quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  36,55,Indeed today the inhabitants of paradise rejoice in their engagements
  36,56,"—they and their mates, reclining on couches in the shades"
  36,57,"There they have fruits, and they have whatever they want"
  36,58,‘Peace!’—a watchword from the all-merciful Lord
  36,59,"And ‘Get apart today, you guilty ones!’"
  36,60,"‘Did I not exhort you, O children of Adam, saying, “Do not worship Satan. He is indeed your manifest enemy"
  36,61,Worship Me. That is a straight path”
  36,62,"Certainly, he has led astray many of your generations. Have you not exercised your reason"
  36,63,This is the hell you had been promised
  36,64,"Enter it today, because of what you used to deny"
  36,65,"Today We shall seal their mouths, and their hands shall speak to Us, and their feet shall bear witness concerning what they used to earn.’"
  36,66,"Had We wished We would have blotted out their eyes: then, were they to advance towards the path, how would have they seen"
  36,67,And had We wished We would have deformed them in their place; then they would neither have been able to move ahead nor to return
  36,68,"And whomever We give a long life, We cause him to regress in creation. Then, will they not exercise their reason"
  36,69,"We did not teach him poetry, nor does it behoove him. This is just a reminder and a manifest Quran"
  36,70,"so that anyone who is alive may be warned, and that the word may come due against the faithless"